Put the following lines in a .bat file to batch render them

Linux/Mac: 
blender -b "/path/to/file_01.blend" -x 1 -a
blender -b "/path/to/file_01.blend" -x 1 -a


Windows:
"C:\Program Files\Blender Foundation\Blender\blender.exe" -b "C:\Path\To\File_01.blend" -x 1 -a
"C:\Program Files\Blender Foundation\Blender\blender.exe" -b "C:\Path\To\File_02.blend" -x 1 -a


-b = render in the background
-x = let blender worry about the extensions of the rendered files
-a = render animation


Start rendering:

Linux/Mac
In terminal type batfile.bat

Windows (Powershell)
Shift right-click in the folder with the .bat file and choose 'open Powershell here'.
Type .\batfile.bat
